HEADWORD: Bougie dcimale
<hw>Bou*gie" d⟦eacute⟧`ci`male"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[F., lit.,
decimal candle.]</ety> <def>A photometric standard used in France,
having the value of one twentieth of the Violle platinum standard, or
